description:
Speaker: Rachel Berryman, Dânia Meira

Track:PyData
Everyday there is a new package or algorithm to use- it can be hard to determine what is useful and what is only hype. The speakers offer a practical roadmap and checklist  to help you cut through the hype and focus on developing useful ML products.

Recorded at the PyConDE & PyData Berlin 2019 conference.
https://pycon.de

More details at the conference page: https://de.pycon.org/program/KC99NY
Twitter:  https://twitter.com/pydataberlin
Twitter:  https://twitter.com/pyconde
title: Avoiding ML FOBO
